## 🎯 Quick Start (5 minutes)

```bash
# 1. Install
npm install super-auth-helper express jsonwebtoken redis dotenv

# 2. Copy files
cp auth-middleware.js src/middleware/
cp .env.example .env

# 3. Generate secrets
node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"
# Copy output → JWT_SECRET in .env
node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"
# Copy output → JWT_REFRESH_SECRET in .env

# 4. Use in your app
const { initializeAuthMiddleware } = require('./middleware/auth-middleware');
const auth = await initializeAuthMiddleware();

# 5. Protect routes
app.get('/api/protected', auth.requireAuth(), handler);
```

